cdx6500PPCTVoicePortTable.name: cdx6500PPCTVoicePortTable
cdx6500PPCTVoicePortTable.description: This table contains the port configuration parameters to configure the DSPM/E&M, DSPM/FXS, DSPM/HC, and DSPM/SM.

cdx6500PPCTVoicePortEntry.name: cdx6500PPCTVoicePortEntry
cdx6500PPCTVoicePortEntry.description: A Voice Port Configuration Table Entry. Each entry contains the configuration parameters for a single Voice Port.

cdx6500VoiceCfgPortNumber.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgPortNumber
cdx6500VoiceCfgPortNumber.description: Port number of the Voice port.

cdx6500VoiceCfgPortType.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgPortType
cdx6500VoiceCfgPortType.description: This parameter represents the port type of the port. voice :This is a voice port.

cdx6500VoiceCfgInterfaceType.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgInterfaceType
cdx6500VoiceCfgInterfaceType.description: Select one of the following physical interfaces being used for this port. The entry must match the hardware. eAndM2 :2 wire E&M (Ear and Mouth) Interface. eAndM4 :4 wire E&M (Ear and Mouth) Interface. fxo :FXO (Foreign Exchange Office ) Interface. fxs :FXS (Foreign Exchange Station) Interface. nc :Skipped during configuration. eAndM2 is only displayed for port numbers 1..54.

cdx6500VoiceCfgSignalingType.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgSignalingType
cdx6500VoiceCfgSignalingType.description: Select the E&M signalling type. i : EandMTypeI. ii : EandMTypeII. v : EandMTypeV. iii : EandMTypeIII. nc : Skipped during configuration. This parameter is displayed for DSPM/E&M and skipped for FXS, FXO, and all virtual port types.

cdx6500VoiceCfgELeadFilter.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgELeadFilter
cdx6500VoiceCfgELeadFilter.description: Selection for E lead filter enable or disable option. disabled : Disables E-lead filter. enabled : Enables E-lead filter. nc : Skipped during configuration. This parameter is displayed for DSPM/E&M and skipped for FXS, FXO, and all virtual port types.

cdx6500VoiceCfgHybridFXS.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgHybridFXS
cdx6500VoiceCfgHybridFXS.description: Hybrid balance filters and termination type based on country. sixHundred : 600 ohm interface for USA, Japan and Ireland. canada : 600 ohms with 2.16 uF germany : 220 ohms in series with (820 ohms in parallel with 115nF). uk : 300 ohms in series with (1K ohms in parallel with 220nF). belgium : 150 ohms in series with (830 ohms in parallel with 72nF). france : 215 ohms in series with (1K ohms in parallel with 137nF). nc : Skipped during configuration. This parameter is displayed for DSPM/FXS and skipped for DSPM/E&M, DSPM/HC(FXO) and all virtual port types.

cdx6500VoiceCfgHybridEAndM2.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgHybridEAndM2
cdx6500VoiceCfgHybridEAndM2.description: Hybrid balance filters and termination type based on country. (Only for E&M-2wire interfaces.) sixHundred : 600 ohm interface for USA, Japan and Ireland. germany : 220 ohms in series with (820 ohms in parallel with 115nF). uk : 370 ohms in series with (620 ohms in parallel with 310nF). nc : Skipped during configuration.

cdx6500VoiceCfgSignalingMode.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgSignalingMode
cdx6500VoiceCfgSignalingMode.description: Select the voice signalling mode. normal : Allows signalling to pass end to end and signalling will be used to control circuit state and packet flow. none : A permanent voice path is established and packet flow is always enabled, but no signalling will be passed through. nc : Skipped during configuration.

cdx6500VoiceCfgSignalingControl.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgSignalingControl
cdx6500VoiceCfgSignalingControl.description: Select signaling control transmission mode in E&M interface type. immediate : Digits are transmitted immediately. wink : Digits are transmitted after the WINK pulse. transparent : The voice signalling states are transmitted end to end without interpreting the signalling state. delay : Digits are transmitted after the end of the Delay Dial signal. masterColisee : 65xx is simulating Colisee master mode. slaveColisee : 65xx is simulating Colisee slave mode. seizureAcknowledge : Transmit Seizure acknowledge immediately after receiving a Seizure signal from the PBX. nc : Skipped during configuration. The parameter will be skipped for FXO & FXS type interface.

cdx6500VoiceCfgNoOfDigitsToCollect.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgNoOfDigitsToCollect
cdx6500VoiceCfgNoOfDigitsToCollect.description: Select number of digits to collect before making a call. The parameter will not be supported.

cdx6500VoiceCfgNoOfRings.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgNoOfRings
cdx6500VoiceCfgNoOfRings.description: Number of rings to be received before a call can be accepted. This parameter is displayed for FXO and skipped for E&M and FXS interface types. A value of 0 implies that this parameter was skipped during configuration.

cdx6500VoiceCfgPCMMode.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgPCMMode
cdx6500VoiceCfgPCMMode.description: Select the PCM encoder/decoder mode. aLaw :PCM encoder/decoder mode = A Law. muLaw :PCM encoder/decoder mode = Mu Law. nc :Skipped during configuration.

cdx6500VoiceCfgCompressionRate.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgCompressionRate
cdx6500VoiceCfgCompressionRate.description: Select the voice compression rate to be used by the DSP. cD8K : 8k CVSELP c16k : 16k CVSELP cBD8K : Bundled 8k CVSELP cB16k : Bundled 16k CVSELP. cE8Kb : Enhanced Bundled 8k CVSELP cE16Kb : Enhanced Bundled 16k CVSELP nc : Skipped during configuration.

cdx6500VoiceCfgDSIControl.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgDSIControl
cdx6500VoiceCfgDSIControl.description: Select if the Digital Speech Interpolation (Silence Detector) will be used with this channel. enabled : DSI is activated. disabled : DSI is not used. nc : Skipped during configuration.

cdx6500VoiceCfgSmoothingDelay.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgSmoothingDelay
cdx6500VoiceCfgSmoothingDelay.description: Select maximum inter packet arrival jitter due to network in milliseconds.

cdx6500VoiceCfgEchoControl.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgEchoControl
cdx6500VoiceCfgEchoControl.description: Select echo control. disabled : Echo pass through. enabled : This enables echo control logic. nc : Skipped during configuration. Echo not detected and not cancelled. This parameter will be skipped in normal mode and only displayed when DEBUG is turned on.

cdx6500VoiceCfgEchoReturnLoss.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgEchoReturnLoss
cdx6500VoiceCfgEchoReturnLoss.description: Select echo return loss in dBm. minus3 : -3 dBm. minus6 : -6 dBm. minus9 : -9 dBm. minus12 : -12dBm. nc :Skipped during configuration.

cdx6500VoiceCfgTxInputSignalLevel.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgTxInputSignalLevel
cdx6500VoiceCfgTxInputSignalLevel.description: Enter the input signal level. To be specified in steps of 0.5 dBm FXO Interface Type : 600 Ohms +6.0 to -2.5dbm 600 Ohms Adaptive +6.0 to -2.5dbm FXS Interface Type : 600 Ohms +6.0 to -6.0dbm Canada +6.0 to -5.5dbm UK +4.5 to -7.5dbm Germany +4.0 to -8.0dbm France -2.0 to -9.0dbm Belgium +4.0 to -8.0dbm E&M Interface Type : 4-Wire/600 +7.0 to -16.0dbm 2-Wire/600 +7.0 to -16.0dbm 2-Wire/UK +5.0 to -16.0dbm 2-Wire/Germany +5.0 to -16.0dbm Virtual Ports(100 and above): +8.0 to -6.0dbm Entering a negative number for the 'Input Signal Level' will result in the DSPM card amplifying the signal by that many dB. Entering a positive number for the 'Input Signal Level' will result in the DSPM card attenuating the signal by that many dB.

cdx6500VoiceCfgRxOutputSignalLevel.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgRxOutputSignalLevel
cdx6500VoiceCfgRxOutputSignalLevel.description: Enter the output signal level. To be selected in steps of 0.5 dBm. FXO Interface Type : 600 Ohms +0.0 to -8.0dbm 600 Ohms Adaptive +0.0 to -8.0dbm FXS Interface Type : 600 Ohms +0.0 to -9.0dbm Canada +0.0 to -9.0dbm UK -1.5 to -9.0dbm Germany -2.0 to -9.0dbm France -1.5 to -9.0dbm Belgium -1.5 to -9.0dbm E&M Interface Type : 4-Wire/600 +7.0 to -16.0dbm 2-Wire/600 +3.0 to -16.0dbm 2-Wire/UK +1.0 to -16.0dbm 2-Wire/Germany +0.0 to -16.0dbm Virtual Ports(100 and above): +6.0 to -8.0dbm Entering a negative number for the 'Output Signal Level' will result in the DSPM card attenuating the signal by that many dB. Entering a positive number for the 'Output Signal Level' will result in the DSPM card amplifying the signal by that many dB.

cdx6500VoiceCfgFaxSupport.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgFaxSupport
cdx6500VoiceCfgFaxSupport.description: This parameter selects whether the FAX data is to be supported. disabled : FAX data will not be detected. enabled : Detects presence of FAX data. nc : Skipped during configuration.

cdx6500VoiceCfgFaxRates.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgFaxRates
cdx6500VoiceCfgFaxRates.description: Specify the speed to switch to, when FAX data is detected. This parameter is ignored if Fax support was disabled. fr9600 : FAX to be transmitted across the network at 9600 bits per second. fr4800 : FAX to be transmitted across the network at 4800 bits per second. nc : Skipped during configuration.

cdx6500VoiceCfgVoiceBandDetection.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgVoiceBandDetection
cdx6500VoiceCfgVoiceBandDetection.description: Modem data detection. yes : Detection of modem data enabled. no : Detection of modem data disabled. nc : Skipped during configuration. This parameter will be skipped in normal mode.Displayed only when DEBUG is turned on.

cdx6500VoiceCfgAutoCallMnemonic.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgAutoCallMnemonic
cdx6500VoiceCfgAutoCallMnemonic.description: This mnemonic name is used to originate the call. It consists of 0 - 8 alphanumeric characters.

cdx6500VoiceCfgCallControl.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgCallControl
cdx6500VoiceCfgCallControl.description: Select calling method. offhook : Call only when Offhook.Disconnect on Onhook. auto : SVC does not depend on On/Offhook condition.It remains established permanently after the power-up. switched : Call only when interface goes offhook and disconnect call when interface goes onhook. Destination is determined by the DTMF digits received. nc : Skipped during configuration.

cdx6500VoiceCfgAutoCallTimeout.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgAutoCallTimeout
cdx6500VoiceCfgAutoCallTimeout.description: Time interval between two successive calls in case of failure of previous call.Used only in `Auto' call control mode.This parameter will be skipped if Call Control is Offhook and Switched.

cdx6500VoiceCfgCallRetries.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgCallRetries
cdx6500VoiceCfgCallRetries.description: Enter maximum number of call retries when previous call failed.Used only in Auto Call Control mode.'0' means try forever. This parameter will be skipped if Call Control is Offhook and Switched.

cdx6500VoiceCfgGroupSubaddress.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgGroupSubaddress
cdx6500VoiceCfgGroupSubaddress.description: Specifies a port subaddress that is shared by several Voice ports. Incoming calls with this subaddress are routed to one of several ports sharing this subaddress. Another name for the group of ports with the same Group Subaddress is Hunt Group.

cdx6500VoiceCfgBilling.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgBilling
cdx6500VoiceCfgBilling.description: This controls whether billing (accounting) records will be created for calls on this port. enabled : Billing is enabled. disabled : Billing is disabled. nc : Skipped during configuration.

cdx6500VoiceCfgRxSignalingStateChangeFil.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgRxSignalingStateChangeFilter
cdx6500VoiceCfgRxSignalingStateChangeFil.description: The amount of time to declare a valid supervisory signaling state change. The granularity is 10 milliseconds.

cdx6500VoiceCfgT1E1RxIdleOnhookState.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgT1E1RxIdleOnhookState
cdx6500VoiceCfgT1E1RxIdleOnhookState.description: The signalling state that represents the idle state. For E1 ports and T1 ESF ports, these bits represent the ABCD signalling bits on the interface. For T1 SF ports these bits represent ABAB signalling bits. `x' means don't care.The range is from 0000 to 1111.

cdx6500VoiceCfgT1E1TxIdleOnhookState.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgT1E1TxIdleOnhookState
cdx6500VoiceCfgT1E1TxIdleOnhookState.description: The signalling state that represents the idle state. For E1 ports and T1 ESF ports, these bits represent the ABCD signalling bits on the interface. For T1 SF ports these bits represent ABAB signalling bits. The range is from 0000 to 1111.

cdx6500VoiceCfgT1E1RxActiveOffhookState.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgT1E1RxActiveOffhookState
cdx6500VoiceCfgT1E1RxActiveOffhookState.description: The signalling state that represents the active state. For E1 ports and T1 ESF ports, these bits represent the ABCD signalling bits on the interface. For T1 SF ports these bits represent ABAB signalling bits. ` x' means don't care. The range is from 0000 to 1111.

cdx6500VoiceCfgT1E1TxActiveOffhookState.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgT1E1TxActiveOffhookState
cdx6500VoiceCfgT1E1TxActiveOffhookState.description: The signalling state that represents the active state. For E1 ports and T1 ESF ports, these bits represent the ABCD signalling bits on the interface. The range is from 0000 to 1111.

cdx6500VoiceCfgT1E1RingingState.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgT1E1RingingState
cdx6500VoiceCfgT1E1RingingState.description: The signalling state that represents the ringing state. For E1 ports and T1 ESF ports, these bits represent the ABCD signalling bits on the interface. For T1 SF ports these bits represent ABAB signalling bits. `x' means don't care. The range is from 0000 to 1111.

cdx6500VoiceCfgT1E1NoRingingState.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgT1E1NoRingingState
cdx6500VoiceCfgT1E1NoRingingState.description: The signalling state that represents the no ringing state. For E1 ports and T1 ESF ports, these bits represent the ABCD signalling bits on the interface. For T1 SF ports these bits represent ABAB signalling bits. `x' means don't care. The range is from 0000 to 1111.

cdx6500VoiceCfgRxWinkStartTimer.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgRxWinkStartTimer
cdx6500VoiceCfgRxWinkStartTimer.description: This is the maximum time to wait for the beginning of the wink signal from the PBX before declaring a wink start malfunction. Granularity is 50 milliseconds.

cdx6500VoiceCfgRxMinimumReceiveWink.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgRxMinimumReceiveWink
cdx6500VoiceCfgRxMinimumReceiveWink.description: The amount of time required to declare a valid wink. Granularity is 10 milliseconds.

cdx6500VoiceCfgRxCalledEndGlareDetect.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgRxCalledEndGlareDetect
cdx6500VoiceCfgRxCalledEndGlareDetect.description: The length of time when a wink pulse will be detected as a glare condition. Granularity is 50 milliseconds.

cdx6500VoiceCfgRxFirstDigitTimer.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgRxFirstDigitTimer
cdx6500VoiceCfgRxFirstDigitTimer.description: The maximum time (in seconds) to wait for the first DTMF digit before declaring a `busyout' state. Granularity is 1 second.

cdx6500VoiceCfgRxInterdigitTimer.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgRxInterdigitTimer
cdx6500VoiceCfgRxInterdigitTimer.description: This is the maximum time (in seconds) to wait for a subsequent receive digit before declaring a misdial. Granularity is 1 second.

cdx6500VoiceCfgTxWinkDelay.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgTxWinkDelay
cdx6500VoiceCfgTxWinkDelay.description: The time delay from receiving a valid Offhook state to start transmitting a wink. Granularity is 10 milliseconds.

cdx6500VoiceCfgTxWinkWidth.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgTxWinkWidth
cdx6500VoiceCfgTxWinkWidth.description: The width of the transmitted wink pulse. Granularity is 10 milliseconds.

cdx6500VoiceCfgTxDigitDelay.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgTxDigitDelay
cdx6500VoiceCfgTxDigitDelay.description: The time delay before transmitting the first DTMF digit after a wink is received.Granularity is 10 milliseconds.

cdx6500VoiceCfgTxDigitOn.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgTxDigitOn
cdx6500VoiceCfgTxDigitOn.description: The time DTMF digits are transmitted. Granularity is 10 milliseconds.

cdx6500VoiceCfgTxInterdigitTime.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgTxInterdigitTime
cdx6500VoiceCfgTxInterdigitTime.description: The time between transmitting DTMF digits. Granularity is 10 milliseconds.

cdx6500VoiceCfgRxInterringWait.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgRxInterringWait
cdx6500VoiceCfgRxInterringWait.description: This is the maximum time to wait for subsequent receive rings before declaring a call abandoned condition. Granularity is 1 second.

cdx6500VoiceCfgRxRingStateChangeFilter.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgRxRingStateChangeFilter
cdx6500VoiceCfgRxRingStateChangeFilter.description: The amount of time to declare the change in the ring state. Granularity is 50 milliseconds.

cdx6500VoiceCfgTxRingerOffLong.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgTxRingerOffLong
cdx6500VoiceCfgTxRingerOffLong.description: This timer is the long off period for ringer cadences that have a short and long off period.For the cases where the ring cadence defines one off period, the Tx Ringer Off Long must be equal to Tx Ringer Off Short. Granularity is 50 milliseconds.

cdx6500VoiceCfgTxRingerOffShort.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgTxRingerOffShort
cdx6500VoiceCfgTxRingerOffShort.description: This timer is the short off period for ringer cadences that have a short and long off period.For the cases where the ring cadence defines one off period, the Tx Ringer Off Long must be equal to Tx Ringer Off Short. Granularity is 50 milliseconds.

cdx6500VoiceCfgTxRingerOn.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgTxRingerOn
cdx6500VoiceCfgTxRingerOn.description: The time of the ringer on pulse. Granularity is 50 milliseconds.

cdx6500VoiceCfgRxDisconnectTimer.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgRxDisconnectTimer
cdx6500VoiceCfgRxDisconnectTimer.description: The amount of time required to receive idle signaling to disconnect a call. For an analog FXO port, RX idle signaling is the loss of loop current. For a FXS port, RX idle signaling is when the interface goes onhook. For an analog E&M port, RX idle signaling is when the 'M' lead goes idle. For digital interfaces, the RX idle state is defined by the 'T1/E1 Rx Idle (on-hook) State' parameter.

cdx6500VoiceCfgRxCalledEndDisconnectDela.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgRxCalledEndDisconnectDelayTimer
cdx6500VoiceCfgRxCalledEndDisconnectDela.description: The additional amount of time beyond the Rx Disconnect filter the calling end must be Onhook to disconnect a call. Granularity is 1 second.

cdx6500VoiceCfgLineErrorRecovery.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgLineErrorRecovery
cdx6500VoiceCfgLineErrorRecovery.description: The length of time voice will be suppressed after LOS or OF condition clears.Granularity is 10 milliseconds. This parameter will be displayed for virtual ports only.

cdx6500VoiceCfgSignalingSampleRate.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgSignalingSampleRate
cdx6500VoiceCfgSignalingSampleRate.description: The time between sampling received signalling states and line states.Granularity is 1 millisecond. This parameter will be displayed only when the DEBUG flag is set.

cdx6500VoiceCfgWaitForParams.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgWaitForParams
cdx6500VoiceCfgWaitForParams.description: The amount of time to wait for a message to set the parameters after receiving a disconnect message (messages occur in the form of an event) before busying out the port. Granularity is 1 second. This parameter will be displayed only when the DEBUG flag is set.

cdx6500VoiceCfgSpareTimer1.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgSpareTimer1
cdx6500VoiceCfgSpareTimer1.description: Spare timer number 1.Granularity is 1 millisecond.This parameter will be displayed only when the DEBUG flag is set.

cdx6500VoiceCfgSpareTimer2.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgSpareTimer2
cdx6500VoiceCfgSpareTimer2.description: Spare timer number 2.Granularity is 1 millisecond. This parameter will be displayed only when the DEBUG flag is set.

cdx6500VoiceCfgTxInterdigitPauseTime.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgTxInterdigitPauseTime
cdx6500VoiceCfgTxInterdigitPauseTime.description: The time between transmitting DTMF digits. Enter in steps of 10 msec.

cdx6500VoiceCfgRxMinimumFlashHookTime.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgRxMinimumFlashHookTime
cdx6500VoiceCfgRxMinimumFlashHookTime.description: The shortest length of time required to be onhook to be recognized as a flash-hook. This value must be less than Rx Maximum Flash-Hook Time for flash-hook to be recognized.

cdx6500VoiceCfgRxMaximumFlashHookTime.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgRxMaximumFlashHookTime
cdx6500VoiceCfgRxMaximumFlashHookTime.description: The longest length of time to be onhook to be recognized as a flash-hook. This value must be less than Rx Disconnect Timer for flash-hook to be recognized. Note: the average of the minimum and maximum flash-hook values will be the pulse width for a transmitted flash-hook.

cdx6500VoiceCfgTransparentSignalingIdleS.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgTransparentSignalingIdleState
cdx6500VoiceCfgTransparentSignalingIdleS.description: The received signalling state that represents the idle state. For E1 ports and T1 ESF ports, these bits represent the ABCD signalling bits on the interface.`x' means don't care. For E&M analog ports, Onhook is assumed for the idle state. The range is 0000 to 1111.

cdx6500VoiceCfgTransparentRxDisconnectFi.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgTransparentRxDisconnectFilter
cdx6500VoiceCfgTransparentRxDisconnectFi.description: The time the received signaling state must be equal to the idle state to disconnect the voice call. Zero value disables idle state disconnect and maintains the voice call in the answered state.Time is entered in minutes.

cdx6500VoiceCfgTransparentSignalingBusyo.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgTransparentSignalingBusyoutState
cdx6500VoiceCfgTransparentSignalingBusyo.description: The received signalling state that represents the Busyout state. For E1 ports and T1 ESF ports, these bits represent the ABCD signalling bits on the interface.For E&M analog ports, Offhook is assumed for the busyout/alarm state. The range is 0000 to 1111.

If the local port is an analog E&M port, enter 0000 for idle (Onhook) and 1111 for active (Offhook). The range is 0000 to 1111.

cdx6500VoiceCfgDialToneLowerFrequency.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgDialToneLowerFrequency
cdx6500VoiceCfgDialToneLowerFrequency.description: The lower of the two frequencies needed to generate the dial tone.

cdx6500VoiceCfgDialToneLowerFrequencyAmp.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgDialToneLowerFrequencyAmplitude
cdx6500VoiceCfgDialToneLowerFrequencyAmp.description: The amplitude of the lower frequency to generate the dial tone. To be specified in steps of 0.5dB, -30dB turn off output. The range is from -30dBm to -3dBm.

cdx6500VoiceCfgDialToneUpperFrequency.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgDialToneUpperFrequency
cdx6500VoiceCfgDialToneUpperFrequency.description: The higher of the two frequencies needed to generate the dial tone.

cdx6500VoiceCfgDialToneUpperFrequencyAmp.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgDialToneUpperFrequencyAmplitude
cdx6500VoiceCfgDialToneUpperFrequencyAmp.description: The amplitude of the upper frequency to generate the dial tone. To be specified in steps of 0.5dB, -30dB turn off output. The range is from -30dBm to -3dBm.

cdx6500VoiceCfgRingBackToneLowerFrequenc.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgRingBackToneLowerFrequency
cdx6500VoiceCfgRingBackToneLowerFrequenc.description: The lower of the two frequencies needed to generate the Ringback tone.

cdx6500VoiceCfgRingBackToneLowerFrequenc.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgRingBackToneLowerFrequencyAmplitude
cdx6500VoiceCfgRingBackToneLowerFrequenc.description: The amplitude of the lower frequency to generate the Ringback tone. To be specified in steps of 0.5dB, -30dB turn off output.The range is from -30dBm to -3dBm.

cdx6500VoiceCfgRingBackToneUpperFrequenc.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgRingBackToneUpperFrequency
cdx6500VoiceCfgRingBackToneUpperFrequenc.description: The higher of the two frequencies needed to generate the Ring-back tone.

cdx6500VoiceCfgRingBackToneUpperFrequenc.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgRingBackToneUpperFrequencyAmplitude
cdx6500VoiceCfgRingBackToneUpperFrequenc.description: The amplitude of the upper frequency to generate the Ringback tone. To be specified in steps of 0.5dB, -30dB turn off output. The range is from -30dBm to -3dBm.

cdx6500VoiceCfgBusyToneLowerFrequency.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgBusyToneLowerFrequency
cdx6500VoiceCfgBusyToneLowerFrequency.description: The lower of the two frequencies needed to generate the Busy tone.

cdx6500VoiceCfgBusyToneLowerFrequencyAmp.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgBusyToneLowerFrequencyAmplitude
cdx6500VoiceCfgBusyToneLowerFrequencyAmp.description: The amplitude of the lower frequency to generate the Busy tone. To be specified in steps of 0.5dB, -30dB turn off output. The range is from -30dBm to -3dBm.

cdx6500VoiceCfgBusyToneUpperFrequency.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgBusyToneUpperFrequency
cdx6500VoiceCfgBusyToneUpperFrequency.description: The higher of the two frequencies needed to generate the Busy tone.

cdx6500VoiceCfgBusyToneUpperFrequencyAmp.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgBusyToneUpperFrequencyAmplitude
cdx6500VoiceCfgBusyToneUpperFrequencyAmp.description: The amplitude of the upper frequency to generate the Busy tone. To be specified in steps of 0.5dB, -30dB turn off output. The range is from -30dBm to -3dBm.

cdx6500VoiceCfgTxBusyToneOffTime.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgTxBusyToneOffTime
cdx6500VoiceCfgTxBusyToneOffTime.description: Timer for the Busy tone off state. Granularity is 50 milliseconds.

cdx6500VoiceCfgTxBusyToneOnTime.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgTxBusyToneOnTime
cdx6500VoiceCfgTxBusyToneOnTime.description: Timer for the busy tone on state. Granularity is 50 milliseconds.

cdx6500VoiceCfgFastBusyToneLowerFrequenc.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgFastBusyToneLowerFrequency
cdx6500VoiceCfgFastBusyToneLowerFrequenc.description: The lower of the two frequencies needed to generate the Fast Busy tone.

cdx6500VoiceCfgFastBusyToneLowerFrequenc.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgFastBusyToneLowerFrequencyAmplitude
cdx6500VoiceCfgFastBusyToneLowerFrequenc.description: The amplitude of the lower frequency to generate the Fast Busy tone. To be specified in steps of 0.5dB, -30dB turn off output. The range is from -30dBm to -3dBm.

cdx6500VoiceCfgFastBusyToneUpperFrequenc.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgFastBusyToneUpperFrequency
cdx6500VoiceCfgFastBusyToneUpperFrequenc.description: The higher of the two frequencies needed to generate the Fast Busy tone.

cdx6500VoiceCfgFastBusyToneUpperFrequenc.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgFastBusyToneUpperFrequencyAmplitude
cdx6500VoiceCfgFastBusyToneUpperFrequenc.description: The amplitude of the upper frequency to generate the Fast Busy tone. To be specified in steps of 0.5dB, -30dB turn off output. The range is from -30dBm to -3dBm.

cdx6500VoiceCfgTxFastBusyToneOffTime.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgTxFastBusyToneOffTime
cdx6500VoiceCfgTxFastBusyToneOffTime.description: Timer for the Fast Busy tone off state. Granularity is 50 milliseconds.

cdx6500VoiceCfgTxFastBusyToneOnTime.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgTxFastBusyToneOnTime
cdx6500VoiceCfgTxFastBusyToneOnTime.description: Timer for the Fast Busy tone on state. Granularity is 50 milliseconds.

cdx6500VoiceCfgHybridFXO.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgHybridFXO
cdx6500VoiceCfgHybridFXO.description: Hybrid balance filters. sixHundred : 600 ohm interface. adaptive : 600 ohm with adaptive filter. nc : Skipped during configuration. This parameter is displayed for DSPM/HC (FXO) and skipped for DSPM/E&M, DSPM/FXS and all virtual port types.

cdx6500VoiceCfgTxPulse.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgTxPulse
cdx6500VoiceCfgTxPulse.description: The width of the transmitted Seizure, PTS, or Answer pulse in msec.

cdx6500VoiceCfgRxMinPulse.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgRxMinPulse
cdx6500VoiceCfgRxMinPulse.description: The minimum pulse width to declare a valid received Seizure, PTS, or Answer pulse.

cdx6500VoiceCfgRxMaxPulse.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgRxMaxPulse
cdx6500VoiceCfgRxMaxPulse.description: The maximum pulse width to declare a valid received Seizure, PTS, or Answer.

cdx6500VoiceCfgTxMasterClear.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgTxMasterClear
cdx6500VoiceCfgTxMasterClear.description: The width of the transmitted Master Clear-Forward, Clear-Back, or Release Guard pulse in msec.

cdx6500VoiceCfgRxMinMasterClear.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgRxMinMasterClear
cdx6500VoiceCfgRxMinMasterClear.description: The minimum pulse width to declare a valid received Master Clear-Forward, Clear-Back, or Release Guard.

cdx6500VoiceCfgRxMaxMasterClear.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgRxMaxMasterClear
cdx6500VoiceCfgRxMaxMasterClear.description: The maximum pulse width to declare a valid received Master Clear-Forward, Clear-Back, or Release Guard.

cdx6500VoiceCfgTxSlaveClear.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgTxSlaveClear
cdx6500VoiceCfgTxSlaveClear.description: The width of the transmitted Slave Clear-Forward or Clear-Back pulse in msec.

cdx6500VoiceCfgRxMinSlaveClear.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgRxMinSlaveClear
cdx6500VoiceCfgRxMinSlaveClear.description: The minimum pulse width to declare a valid received Slave Clear-Forward or Clear-Back.

cdx6500VoiceCfgRxMaxSlaveClear.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgRxMaxSlaveClear
cdx6500VoiceCfgRxMaxSlaveClear.description: The maximum pulse width to declare a valid received Slave Clear-Forward or Clear-Back.

cdx6500VoiceCfgTxSlaveRelease.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgTxSlaveRelease
cdx6500VoiceCfgTxSlaveRelease.description: The width of the transmitted Slave Release Guard pulse in msec.

cdx6500VoiceCfgRxMinSlaveRelease.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgRxMinSlaveRelease
cdx6500VoiceCfgRxMinSlaveRelease.description: The minimum pulse width to declare a valid received Slave Release Guard.

cdx6500VoiceCfgRxMaxSlaveRelease.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgRxMaxSlaveRelease
cdx6500VoiceCfgRxMaxSlaveRelease.description: The maximum pulse width to declare a valid received Slave Release Guard.

cdx6500VoiceCfgTxPTSTime.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgTxPTSTime
cdx6500VoiceCfgTxPTSTime.description: The time delay from receiving a valid Seizure from the PBX to start transmitting a PTS pulse.

cdx6500VoiceCfgRxPTSTime.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgRxPTSTime
cdx6500VoiceCfgRxPTSTime.description: The maximum time to wait for a PTS pulse from the PBX after sending a Seizure before giving up and clearing the trunk.

cdx6500VoiceCfgMasterGuard.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgMasterGuard
cdx6500VoiceCfgMasterGuard.description: The time the master side waits in the guard state after transmitting a clear pulse.

cdx6500VoiceCfgSlaveGuard.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgSlaveGuard
cdx6500VoiceCfgSlaveGuard.description: The time the slave side waits in the guard state after transmitting a clear pulse.

cdx6500VoiceCfgTxFlashHookTime.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgTxFlashHookTime
cdx6500VoiceCfgTxFlashHookTime.description: The lenght of time a flash signal will be transmitted as a result of a flash-hook from the remote interface.

cdx6500VoiceCfgDtmfAmplitude.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgDtmfAmplitude
cdx6500VoiceCfgDtmfAmplitude.description: The amplitude of the DTMF digits. To be specified in steps of 0.5dB, -30.0 turn off output. The range is from -30dBm to -3dBm.

cdx6500VoiceCfgFXSOffhookFilter.name: cdx6500VoiceCfgFXSOffhookFilter
cdx6500VoiceCfgFXSOffhookFilter.description: This is the amoung of time a valid OFFHOOK conidtion must be present before an analog FXS will declare OFFHOOK.

cdx6500GGCTVoiceSwitchTable.name: cdx6500GGCTVoiceSwitchTable
cdx6500GGCTVoiceSwitchTable.description: This table contains the Voice Switch Table configuration.

cdx6500VoiceSwitchEntry.name: cdx6500VoiceSwitchEntry
cdx6500VoiceSwitchEntry.description: Each entry contains a list of parameters that makeup the Voice Switch Table.

cdx6500VoiceSwitchRxDTMFDigitString.name: cdx6500VoiceSwitchRxDTMFDigitString
cdx6500VoiceSwitchRxDTMFDigitString.description: Select the voice number plans for the 6520/6560 network. The received DTMF digits received by the voice interface is compared to this parameter. - Enter a trailing asterisk(*) as a wild-card. - Use the space bar to blank the parameter. Range: 1 to 20 characters (valid characters are 0 through 9, '-', ',', '/', and '*'). The characters '-', ',', and '/' are allowed only for ease of reading. They are not sent to the remote port. Note: The maximum number of digits that can be sent to the remote end is 16.

cdx6500VoiceSwitchNumRxDigitToReceive.name: cdx6500VoiceSwitchNumRxDigitToReceive
cdx6500VoiceSwitchNumRxDigitToReceive.description: Select the number of DTMF digits to be received before making the call request.

cdx6500VoiceSwitchCallParam.name: cdx6500VoiceSwitchCallParam
cdx6500VoiceSwitchCallParam.description: Define the network address of the called node and the port or Hunt Group number of the desired destination port.

cdx6500VoiceSwitchAlternateDestination.name: cdx6500VoiceSwitchAlternateDestination
cdx6500VoiceSwitchAlternateDestination.description: This object is no longer supported.

cdx6500VoiceSwitchCompressionOverrideRat.name: cdx6500VoiceSwitchCompressionOverrideRate
cdx6500VoiceSwitchCompressionOverrideRat.description: Select the voice compression override algorithm. none - No override, use port configured value. c8k - 8k CVSELP c16k - 16k CVSELP cB8k - Bundled 8k CVSELP cB16k - Bundled 16k CVSELP cE8Kb - Enhanced Bundled 8k CVSELP cE8Kb - Enhanced Bundled 16k CVSELP nc - Skipped during configuration.

cdx6500VoiceSwitchNumLeadingDigitToStrip.name: cdx6500VoiceSwitchNumLeadingDigitToStrip
cdx6500VoiceSwitchNumLeadingDigitToStrip.description: Select the number of leading digits to be stripped off the received digits stream before sending the digits stream to the remote port.

cdx6500VoiceSwitchPreFixDigits.name: cdx6500VoiceSwitchPreFixDigits
cdx6500VoiceSwitchPreFixDigits.description: Select digits to be added in front of or at the end of the received stream (after the stripped digits are removed) before sending the digit stream to the remote port. Range: 1 to 20 characters (valid characters are 0 through 9, '*', '#', 'R', 'P', and '-'). The character '-' is allowed only for ease of reading. It is not sent to the remote port. The 'P' character is used to indicate a pause is required in the playout of the digits at the remote end. The length of the pause is equal to 'Tx Interdigit Pause Time' as defined at the called port (destination port). Leading 'P' characters are not supported. The character 'R' is used to separate the prefix digit string from the postfix digit string Note: The maximum number of digits that can be sent to the remote end is 16.

cdx6500VoiceSwitchPostFixDigits.name: cdx6500VoiceSwitchPostFixDigits
cdx6500VoiceSwitchPostFixDigits.description: Select DTMF digits to be added at the end of the received DTMF stream before sending the digit stream to the remote port. Range: 1 to 20 characters (valid characters are 0 through 9, '-', ',', '/', '*', '#', and 'P'). The characters '-', ',', and '/' are allowed only for ease of reading. They are not sent to the remote port. The 'P' character is used to indicate a pause is required in the playout of the digits at the remote end. The length of the pause is equal to 'Tx Interdigit Pause Time' as defined at the called port (destination port). Note: The maximum number of digits that can be sent to the remote end is 16. This object is no longer supported.

cdx6500VoiceSwitchEntryNumber.name: cdx6500VoiceSwitchEntryNumber
cdx6500VoiceSwitchEntryNumber.description: This is the entry number in the Voice Switch Table.

cdx6500PPSTVoicePortTable.name: cdx6500PPSTVoicePortTable
cdx6500PPSTVoicePortTable.description: This table contains the port statistics for Voice ports.

cdx6500PPSTVoicePortEntry.name: cdx6500PPSTVoicePortEntry
cdx6500PPSTVoicePortEntry.description: A Voice Port Statistics Table Entry. Each entry contains the statistics for a single Voice Port.

cdx6500VoiceStatsPortNumber.name: cdx6500VoiceStatsPortNumber
cdx6500VoiceStatsPortNumber.description: Port number of the Voice Port.

cdx6500VoiceStatsPortInterfaceType.name: cdx6500VoiceStatsPortInterfaceType
cdx6500VoiceStatsPortInterfaceType.description: This parameter indicates the type of DPSM card used. eAndM2 : DPSM/E&M. eAndM4 : DPSM/E&M. fxo : DPSM/HC(FXO). fxs : DPSM/FXS.

cdx6500VoiceStatsHWRevAndPartNumber.name: cdx6500VoiceStatsHWRevAndPartNumber
cdx6500VoiceStatsHWRevAndPartNumber.description: Hardware revision and part number of the main card. The revision number has format n.n and the part number is an 8 digit number of the form nnnnnnnn.

cdx6500VoiceStatsFortyEightVolts.name: cdx6500VoiceStatsFortyEightVolts
cdx6500VoiceStatsFortyEightVolts.description: This parameter indicates whether the 48 volt power supply is installed in the node. none : power supply not installed. present : power supply installed. na : Value not available. This parameter will not be displayed for DSPM/HC.

cdx6500VoiceStatsPortState.name: cdx6500VoiceStatsPortState
cdx6500VoiceStatsPortState.description: This parameter indicates ths status of the port. disabled : The port is disabled. enabled : The port is enabled.

cdx6500VoiceStatsCircuitState.name: cdx6500VoiceStatsCircuitState
cdx6500VoiceStatsCircuitState.description: This parameter indicates the state of the SVC associated with this port. connected : SVC established. disconnected : SVC not established.

cdx6500VoiceStatsCurrentMode.name: cdx6500VoiceStatsCurrentMode
cdx6500VoiceStatsCurrentMode.description: This parameter indicates the current operating mode of the DSP. voice : DSP is currently operating in voice mode. pcm : PCM mode is not supported. fax : DSP is currently operating in fax mode.

cdx6500VoiceStatsTimeOfLastStatReset.name: cdx6500VoiceStatsTimeOfLastStatReset
cdx6500VoiceStatsTimeOfLastStatReset.description: This parameter indicates the time since the last statistic reset using the format month:day:year:hours:minutes:seconds (mm:dd:yyyy:hh:mm:ss).

cdx6500VoiceStatsCallDuration.name: cdx6500VoiceStatsCallDuration
cdx6500VoiceStatsCallDuration.description: This parameter indicates the duration of the current (last) call using the format hours:minutes:seconds (hh:mm:ss).

cdx6500VoiceStatsTotalCallDuration.name: cdx6500VoiceStatsTotalCallDuration
cdx6500VoiceStatsTotalCallDuration.description: This parameter indicates the total time of all calls since last reset.It is measured from Offhook to Onhook and uses the format hours:minutes:seconds (hh:mm:ss).

cdx6500VoiceStatsPortUtilization.name: cdx6500VoiceStatsPortUtilization
cdx6500VoiceStatsPortUtilization.description: This parameter is calculated as the ratio of `Total Call Duration' to `Time Of Last Reset'. It is a percentage value of the form nnn%.

cdx6500VoiceStatsNumberOfCalls.name: cdx6500VoiceStatsNumberOfCalls
cdx6500VoiceStatsNumberOfCalls.description: This parameter indicates the total number of calls since the last reset.

cdx6500VoiceStatsLastDigitsTransmitted.name: cdx6500VoiceStatsLastDigitsTransmitted
cdx6500VoiceStatsLastDigitsTransmitted.description: This parameter indicates the last DTMF digits transmitted to the voice interface. Not supported at this time.

cdx6500VoiceStatsLastDigitsReceived.name: cdx6500VoiceStatsLastDigitsReceived
cdx6500VoiceStatsLastDigitsReceived.description: This parameter indicates the last DTMF digits received from the voice interface. Not supported at this time.

cdx6500VoiceStatsTxPacketDropped.name: cdx6500VoiceStatsTxPacketDropped
cdx6500VoiceStatsTxPacketDropped.description: This parameter indicates the number of times transmit packets were dropped due to DSPM congestion.

cdx6500VoiceStatsRxPacketDropped.name: cdx6500VoiceStatsRxPacketDropped
cdx6500VoiceStatsRxPacketDropped.description: This parameter indicates the number of times receive packets were dropped due to network overload or processor loading.

cdx6500VoiceStatsDroppedPackets.name: cdx6500VoiceStatsDroppedPackets
cdx6500VoiceStatsDroppedPackets.description: This parameter indicates the estimate of packets dropped end to end in the network.

cdx6500VoiceStatsDSPInternalFaults.name: cdx6500VoiceStatsDSPInternalFaults
cdx6500VoiceStatsDSPInternalFaults.description: This parameter indicates the number of recoverable software faults.It is displayed only when the DEBUG flag is set.

cdx6500VoiceStatsTxPackets.name: cdx6500VoiceStatsTxPackets
cdx6500VoiceStatsTxPackets.description: This parameter indicates the number of packets received from the network port since the last reset.

cdx6500VoiceStatsRxPackets.name: cdx6500VoiceStatsRxPackets
cdx6500VoiceStatsRxPackets.description: This parameter indicates the number of packets sent to the network port since the last reset.

cdx6500VoiceStatsTxPacketsPerSecond.name: cdx6500VoiceStatsTxPacketsPerSecond
cdx6500VoiceStatsTxPacketsPerSecond.description: This parameter indicates the average number of packets transmitted per second.It is calculated as the ratio of `Tx Packets' to `Total Call Duration'.

cdx6500VoiceStatsRxPacketsPerSecond.name: cdx6500VoiceStatsRxPacketsPerSecond
cdx6500VoiceStatsRxPacketsPerSecond.description: This parameter indicates the average number of packets received per second.It is calculated as the ratio of `Rx Packets' to `Total Call Duration'.

cdx6500VoiceStatsDSIEfficiency.name: cdx6500VoiceStatsDSIEfficiency
cdx6500VoiceStatsDSIEfficiency.description: This parameter is calculated by dividing `Rx Packets/sec' by the packet rate. It is a percentage value.

cdx6500VoiceStatsCurrentRate.name: cdx6500VoiceStatsCurrentRate
cdx6500VoiceStatsCurrentRate.description: This parameter indicates the current compression rate being used. cD8K : Compression rate is 8K. cBD8K : Compression rate is bundled 8K. cE8Kb : Compression rate is Enhanced bundled D8K. cD16K : Compression rate is 16K. cBD16K : Compression rate is bundled 16K. cE16Kb : Compression rate is Enhanced bundled D16K. cPcm : Compression rate is PCM. cFax : Compression rate is FAX. na : Value not available.

cdx6500VoiceStatsInputPower.name: cdx6500VoiceStatsInputPower
cdx6500VoiceStatsInputPower.description: This parameter indicates the input power level in dBm. (Measured power).

cdx6500VoiceStatsOutputPower.name: cdx6500VoiceStatsOutputPower
cdx6500VoiceStatsOutputPower.description: This parameter indicates the output power level in dBm. (Measured power).

cdx6500VoiceStatsFAXTransmissions.name: cdx6500VoiceStatsFAXTransmissions
cdx6500VoiceStatsFAXTransmissions.description: This parameter indicates the number of FAX transmissions spoofed.

cdx6500VoiceStatsUnsupportedFmtsFAXXmiss.name: cdx6500VoiceStatsUnsupportedFmtsFAXXmissions
cdx6500VoiceStatsUnsupportedFmtsFAXXmiss.description: This parameter indicates the number of FAX transmissions requesting unsupported formats but transmitted using ISG formats.

cdx6500PPSTSignalingSequenceTrapTxState.name: cdx6500PPSTSignalingSequenceTrapTxState
cdx6500PPSTSignalingSequenceTrapTxState.description: The transmitting voice signalling state is displayed as ABCD (i.e. 1010). This object is no longer supported. Refer to cdx6500SignalingSequenceTrapTxState.

cdx6500PPSTSignalingSequenceTrapRxState.name: cdx6500PPSTSignalingSequenceTrapRxState
cdx6500PPSTSignalingSequenceTrapRxState.description: The receiving voice signalling state is displayed as ABCD (i.e. 1010). This object is no longer supported. Refer to cdx6500SignalingSequenceTrapRxState.

cdx6500PPSTSignalingSequenceTrapMachineS.name: cdx6500PPSTSignalingSequenceTrapMachineState
cdx6500PPSTSignalingSequenceTrapMachineS.description: The voice signalling state machine state is a 11 character field representing the state of the signalling software. This object is no longer supported. Refer to cdx6500SignalingSequenceTrapMachineState.

cdx6500PPSTSignalingSequenceTrapTimeSinc.name: cdx6500PPSTSignalingSequenceTrapTimeSinceLastChange
cdx6500PPSTSignalingSequenceTrapTimeSinc.description: This parameter indicates the time from the previous state to this state, measured in milliseconds. This object is no longer supported. Refer to cdx6500SignalingSequenceTrapTimeSinceLastChange.

cdx6500PPSTSignalingSequenceTrapComment.name: cdx6500PPSTSignalingSequenceTrapComment
cdx6500PPSTSignalingSequenceTrapComment.description: The comment field is an ASCII string upto 16 characters long. This object is no longer supported. Refer to cdx6500SignalingSequenceTrapComment.

cdx6500VoiceStatsCurrentStatus.name: cdx6500VoiceStatsCurrentStatus
cdx6500VoiceStatsCurrentStatus.description: This is the call processing state machine status. inhibited : Current Status = Disconnected. disconnected : Current Status = Disconnected. calling : Current Status = Calling. called : Current Status = Called. connected : Current Status = Connected (data transfer). null : Current Status = Undefined.

cdx6500VoiceStatsLastClearCauseCode.name: cdx6500VoiceStatsLastClearCauseCode
cdx6500VoiceStatsLastClearCauseCode.description: This parameter indicates the last clear cause code received Every code corresponds to an integer value followed by its text description in paranthesis. eg.Consider the clear cause code for `number busy' which is CAUSE-CLR-NUM-BSY. This corresponds to : 001 (number busy).

cdx6500VoiceStatsLastClearDiagnosticCode.name: cdx6500VoiceStatsLastClearDiagnosticCode
cdx6500VoiceStatsLastClearDiagnosticCode.description: This parameter indicates the last clear diagnostic received.Every code corresponds to an integer value followed by its text description in paranthesis. eg.Consider the diagnostic code for `invalid bits in packet' which is DIAG-INV-PKT-BITS.This corresponds to :041 (invalid bits in packet).

cdx6500VoiceStatsLastInboundCallPacketCa.name: cdx6500VoiceStatsLastInboundCallPacketCalledAddress
cdx6500VoiceStatsLastInboundCallPacketCa.description: This parameter contains the called address present in the last inbound call packet.

cdx6500VoiceStatsLastInboundCallPacketCa.name: cdx6500VoiceStatsLastInboundCallPacketCallingAddress
cdx6500VoiceStatsLastInboundCallPacketCa.description: This parameter contains the calling address present in the last inbound call packet.

cdx6500VoiceStatsLastInboundCallPacketFa.name: cdx6500VoiceStatsLastInboundCallPacketFacilities
cdx6500VoiceStatsLastInboundCallPacketFa.description: This parameter contains the facilities present in the last inbound call packet.

cdx6500VoiceStatsLastInboundCallPacketCU.name: cdx6500VoiceStatsLastInboundCallPacketCUD
cdx6500VoiceStatsLastInboundCallPacketCU.description: This parameter contains the call user data present in the last inbound call packet.

cdx6500VoiceStatsLastOutboundCallPacketC.name: cdx6500VoiceStatsLastOutboundCallPacketCalledAddress
cdx6500VoiceStatsLastOutboundCallPacketC.description: This parameter contains the called address present in the last outbound call packet.

cdx6500VoiceStatsLastOutboundCallPacketC.name: cdx6500VoiceStatsLastOutboundCallPacketCallingAddress
cdx6500VoiceStatsLastOutboundCallPacketC.description: This parameter contains the calling address present in the last outbound call packet.

cdx6500VoiceStatsLastOutboundCallPacketF.name: cdx6500VoiceStatsLastOutboundCallPacketFacilities
cdx6500VoiceStatsLastOutboundCallPacketF.description: This parameter contains the facilities present in the last outbound call packet.

cdx6500VoiceStatsLastOutboundCallPacketC.name: cdx6500VoiceStatsLastOutboundCallPacketCUD
cdx6500VoiceStatsLastOutboundCallPacketC.description: This parameter contains the call user data present in the last outbound call packet.

cdx6500VoiceStatsRingerStatus.name: cdx6500VoiceStatsRingerStatus
cdx6500VoiceStatsRingerStatus.description: This parameter indicates the Ringer status on the board. It is displayed only for DSPM/FXS interfaces. rs25Hz : 25Hz Ringer status on board. rs50Hz : 50Hz Ringer status on board. na : Value not available.

cdx6500VoiceStatsDSPMSMSlotNumber.name: cdx6500VoiceStatsDSPMSMSlotNumber
cdx6500VoiceStatsDSPMSMSlotNumber.description: This parameter indicates the slot of the DSPM/SM. It is displayed only for DSPM/SM interfaces. A value of 0 indicates that this parameter is not available.

cdx6500VoiceStatsDSPMNumber.name: cdx6500VoiceStatsDSPMNumber
cdx6500VoiceStatsDSPMNumber.description: This parameter indicates the DSP used for the virtual port.It is displayed only for DSPM/SM interfaces. A value of 0 indicates that this parameter is not available.
